    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We may solve this problem the same way as Telegram solved it.\n\nWhen a Telegram user sends a message to some other user, they send it more or less anonymously — you can see some basic information that allows you to distinguish one user from another, for example, user's nickname (it can probably be replaced by address in our case), but can't see anything else like username or email or phone. But when you're chatting with someone \"anonymously\", you can always press the button \"Share my contact info\" or \"Add to contacts\" which sends all the profile information to this user.\n",
